<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-369-022  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 369 022  OV: 08 368 994.andM; </DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  April 23 1990 v7 n16 p83(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>The Complete PC Inc. Complete Half-Page Scanner/400. (HardwareReview) (one of eight evaluations of hand-held scanning systems in'Hand-held scanners fit for certain tasks.') (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Halliday, Caroline; Damore, Kelley.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>The Complete PC Inc's $594 Complete Half-Page Scanner/400hand-held scanner is easy to position and roll but suffers fromthe same text-handling frustrations as competing products.andP;  Itcomes with only basic SmartScan scanning software; the extra-costCAT Reader OCR software is fairly easy to use and can scan textfrom top to bottom or left to right.andP;  The Complete Half-PageScanner/400 requires two scans to read a typical 8.5-x-11-inchpage.andP;  CAT Reader automatically merges up to eight side-by-sidescans during the OCR process but tends to do so inaccurately.andO;Buyers like the Half-Page Scanner's maneuverability but note thata steady hand is still required.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Complete PC Inc. (products).andO;Product:   Complete PC Complete Half-Page Scanner-400 (Scanning device).andO;Topic:     ScanningGraphics SystemsEvaluation.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>The Complete PC Inc.andM;THE COMPLETE HALF-PAGE SCANNER/400andM;With its angular shape and two wide rollers in the base of the unit, TheComplete Half-Page Scanner/400 proved the easiest device to position and rollstraight.andP;  However, like the rest of the products here, it may provefrustrating to use for text applications.andM;The Complete Half-Page Scanner/400 is supplied with only basic scanningsoftware, called SmartScan.andP;  It allows users to rotate, crop, scale, mergeand edit the scanned images.andM;The CAT Reader OCR software performed similarly to DFI's Carets/Deluxe OCRsoftware.andP;  While apparently getting slightly lower recognition rates, CATReader is much easier to use than Carets because of its more accessibleinterface.andP;  CAT Reader is supplied with two pretrained font files thatcontain images for several commonly used fonts.andM;Text can be scanned from top to bottom or left to right.andP;  To scan a typical8-1/2-by-11-inch page, two scans must be made; CAT Reader automaticallymerges them during the OCR process.andP;  CAT Reader can merge as many as eightside-by-side scans.andP;  As with the other OCR programs, there were problems withmerging text.andM;The Complete Half-Page Scanner/400 has a resolution switch, labeled 2, 3 and4 (for 200, 300 and 400 dots per inch, respectively), and a brightnessswitch, labeled 1, 2, 3 and 4.andP;  These two switches can be easily confused.andO;The contrast adjustment wheel is well recessed into the case so it cannot beknocked accidentally.andP;  The scan button, on top of the scanner, need only bepressed briefly to indicate the start and end of a scan.andM;The Complete PC Inc., of San Jose, Calif., can be reached at (408) 434-0145.andM;Buyers say ...andM;One buyer pleased with The Complete half-Page Scanner/400 is D.K.andP;  Heller, adesktop-publishing consultant and owner of Corporate Computer Support Group,a software consulting company in Orange, Calif.andP;  Heller uses the scanner toinput store receipts and sheet music.andP;  She primarily scans graphics imagesand does not use OCR software.andM;&quot;The price was good,&quot; she said.andP;  &quot;Furthermore, it gives a wider sweep for ahalf-page scanner.&quot;andP;  Users need a steady hand or a ruler to move the scannerstraight, Heller noted.andP;  However, with practice, mastering scanner movementis not difficult, she said.andM;Dick Palm, vice president of engineering for Voyager Computer Corp., amanufacturer of computer peripherals in Fullerton, Calif., purchased TheComplete Half-Page Scanner/400 after finding Logitech's ScanMan Plusdifficult to maneuver.andM;Palm is satisfied with the product, and uses it to scan photos, sketches andclip art.andP;  &quot;The scanning accuracy is good, and the installation was veryeasy,&quot; he said.andO;</TEXT></DOC>